00:21:41,839 --> 00:21:44,039
JAPANの美術史♪
JAPAN's Art History♪

326
00:21:44,039 --> 00:21:46,139
JAPANの美術史♪
JAPAN's Art History♪

327
00:21:46,139 --> 00:21:47,839
JAPANの美術史♪
JAPAN's Art History♪

328
00:21:47,839 --> 00:21:50,039
お・ぼ・え・ま・SHOW!
Let's learn it all!

329
00:21:50,039 --> 00:21:57,239
さあ、3Dライブの途中ではございますが、ここで日本美術史の授業を始めたいと思います！
Now, even though we are in the middle of our 3D live stream, I would like to begin our Japanese art history lesson!

330
00:21:57,239 --> 00:22:01,239
は〜い皆さんこんにちは！美術史を学ぶ時間です！
Hello everyone! It's time to learn about art history!

331
00:22:01,239 --> 00:22:04,839
まずは縄文 弥生 古墳まで やってみよう！
First, let's explore from Jomon, Yayoi, to Kofun!

332
00:22:04,839 --> 00:22:08,539
火焔型土器、遮光器土偶、縄文のビーナス！
Flame-like vessels, Shako-ki dogu, and the Venus of Jomon!

333
00:22:08,539 --> 00:22:12,139
銅鐸、銅戈、銅矛、銅剣、弥生土器！
Dotaku, Doka, Doho, Doken, and Yayoi pottery!

334
00:22:12,139 --> 00:22:16,339
埴輪も色々、踊る人々、挂甲武人、馬型埴輪！
Various haniwa, dancing people, armored warriors, and horse haniwa!

335
00:22:16,339 --> 00:22:20,639
古墳出土の鉄刀、鉄剣、七支刀に土師器 須恵器！
Iron sabers and swords from Kofun, Seven-Branched Sword, Haji and Sue pottery!

336
00:22:20,639 --> 00:22:24,139
OK OK OK OK、いい感じ！
OK, OK, OK, OK, looking good!

337
00:22:24,139 --> 00:22:28,039
次は飛鳥に奈良時代！ 3、2、1、ゴー！
Next up is the Asuka and Nara periods! 3, 2, 1, go!

338
00:22:28,039 --> 00:22:31,639
仏像いっぱい釈迦如来、菩薩と合わせて三尊像！
Plentiful Buddhist statues like Shaka Nyorai, forming Triads with Bodhisattvas!

339
00:22:31,639 --> 00:22:35,639
玉虫厨子、天寿国繍帳、金堂壁画、古墳壁画！
Tamamushi Shrine, Tenjukoku Shucho tapestry, Kondo murals, and Kofun murals!

340
00:22:35,639 --> 00:22:39,439
東大寺には奈良の大仏、興福寺には阿修羅像！
Great Buddha of Nara at Todai-ji, Ashura statue at Kofuku-ji!

341
00:22:39,439 --> 00:22:41,839
音と一緒に遊びましょう！
Let's play along with the beat!

342
00:22:41,839 --> 00:22:43,639
螺鈿紫檀五絃琵琶！
Raden Shitan Gogen Biwa!

343
00:22:43,639 --> 00:22:47,339
未来のキミに届くように
So it reaches the future you,

344
00:22:47,339 --> 00:22:50,939
